i18n labels: entity and field human labels (gap «Important»)

Entities take an optional label — `entity Incident "Инцидент":` — and fields a
`label="…"` modifier. Both flow through the DSL (parser, AST, model), the
per-actor /api/meta, and the web UI, which now shows the label everywhere an
identifier used to appear (nav, list headers, forms, record view) and falls
back to the raw name when no label is declared. Grammar documents both.

The Service Desk pack is fully Russian-labelled (10 entities + every Incident
field), so the operator UI reads in the user's language instead of English
identifiers — verified live in the browser against seeded Russian data.
